3 questions you should ask before hiring a wedding planner:

Here’s why you should know:

Q1) This information will make it easier to decide what type of planner would be best for you. For example, if you’re super-organized and have time to follow up with pros yourself, then you may only need someone for a coordination role. 

Q2) A wedding planner’s role isn’t just to manage the pros, but also your friends and family, which isn’t as easy as you might think. They should tell you what their system is to make sure everything runs smoothly and on time.

Q3) Back-up plans aren’t just for outdoor weddings. You want to make sure they have someone capable on hand to take over if they get sick or can’t make it that day, like another planner at their company or a seasoned assistant.

When booking your venue with your ceremony and reception in the same space, a room flip most likely will take place. 

Please be advised, depending on the number of tables and chairs, this is a task you don’t want your family and friends to do. 

Before you book your venue, please discuss room flipping service with the venue coordinator. 

Here are a few questions to ask:

1. Do you offer room flipping service? What does it entails?
2. Who moves the centerpieces and personal items during the flip? 
3. How long does it take to flip the room?
4. Is there an additional cost to flip the room?
5. Where will my guests be during the room flip? 

Keep reading:
Flipping a room can take up to an hour, but it can go up to 90 minutes, depending on guests size and details. 

Meanwhile, while this is happening you will be taking photos with your wedding party while your guests is enjoying cocktail hour.

I strongly suggest, you hire a month of coordinator or talk with your planner, because a room flip will greatly increased your labor cost… why? because it takes additional staff to flip a room in a short amount of time. 
Hope this helps!

Wedding Tasting! What is it? 

A wedding tasting is when you taste the menu items, or proposed menu items for your reception. 

Do I need to have one? 
If you’ve never attended a wedding tasting before you probably don’t know what to expect. #Yes!

Food and beverage is such an important and expensive part of your wedding, you want to make sure you get it right. 

If you haven’t selected a caterer yet, this might help you make your decision. If you have already signed a contract with a venue, this gives you the chance to get to know their presentation style and taste their food.

Here are a few tasting tips and questions 
to ponder:

1. Take lots of notes on what you’ve tried
2. When do you need final menu choices and headcount? 
3. How do you handle dietary restrictions and allergies? 
4. The chef preparing the tasting, will it be the same chef on the day of my wedding?
5. Are non-alcoholic beverages included in the food costs? If not, what are those costs? 

Lastly, Offer constructive feedback to the chef, if there is something you want added or removed, tell them exactly what you like and don’t like so they can adjust it.

Happy planning!

* Fruit

How to apply for a marriage license!

A couple wishing to be married in Florida must be prepared to provide their Social Security numbers or any other available identifications such as driver license numbers or other photo IDs (passport, military ID), to the Clerk’s office to apply for a marriage license. 

If either of the couple were previously married, they must provide the exact date of divorce, death or annulment as well as the state and county where the divorce took place.

This post applies to Florida, please check your state’s Clerk office for rules and regulations!

Wedding gifts stolen, what to do?

A few years ago one of my couples were contestants on a reality TV show, 4 brides 4 weddings. During production their wedding gifts were stolen. We never found out who stole them, but trust me, I have an idea what happened.

Every since that incident I immediately put a process in place to ensure my clients wedding gifts remain safe. 

At weddings, there are a lot of people moving around, vendors, guests, family and random people passing by. You never know who may have sticky fingers, you have to be careful not to leave your wedding gifts unattended. 
Here are a few tips to help prevent wedding day theft:
1. Hire a planner, they will keep their eyes on your gift table. 
2. Place your gift table away from any exits to make it difficult for anyone to walk away with your gifts.
3. Assign someone your planner can hand off your envelope box and gifts to. Maybe your parents, best friend or a wedding party member. 
4. Invest in wedding insurance. We recommend Wedsafe, they cover theft.
5. Consider an online registry and have your gifts sent directly to you. 

Ladies and Gentlemen, planning your wedding is fun and exciting, but please keep in mind wedding theft does happen. If it happens to you call the venue, and the police, then call your insurance company.

What if I can’t invite everyone to my wedding?

So I get asked this question a lot. What if I can’t invite all of my co-workers, my church family, my cousins, my neighbors to my wedding, how do I handle it?

Well my first response is, your wedding, your way! Although you would love to invite everyone, it can be costly. Most people get it, they understand that weddings are expensive and know that everyone can’t come. 

So my best advice is to tell all your guests who are invited who’s not invited, especially if they are co-workers are church family. That way, they don’t talk about the wedding and make them feel awkward.

Also, if you are not inviting them to your wedding please don’t invite them to your bridal shower. That may be a little awkward as well. 

Provide your maid of honor or family member with a list for your bridal shower or bachelorette party. 

But don’t sweat it, if people get upset, because they didn’t make the list they will get over it because your friendship should be stronger than one day.

How your wedding vision become reality! 

Let’s talk wedding day venue:🏟

When booking your venue with your ceremony and reception in the same space, a room flip most likely will take place. 

Please be advised, depending on the number of tables and chairs, this is a task you don’t want your family and friends to do. 

Before you book your venue, please discuss room flipping service with the venue coordinator. 

Here are a few questions to ask:

1. Do you offer room flipping service? What does it entails?
2. Who moves the centerpieces and personal items during the flip? 
3. How long does it take to flip the room?
4. Is there an additional cost to flip the room?
5. Where will my guests be during the room flip? 

Keep reading:
Flipping a room can take up to an hour, but it can go up to 90 minutes, depending on guests size and details. 

Meanwhile, while this is happening you will be taking photos with your wedding party while your guests is enjoying cocktail hour.

I strongly suggest, you hire a month of coordinator or talk with your planner, because a room flip will greatly increased your labor cost… why? because it takes additional staff to flip a room in a short amount of time. 
Hope this helps!

Are you familiar with the age old adage that suggests, “once you know better, you do better?” I was talking to an etiquette coach and learned something new…

As an honoree, you should not raise your glass during a toast. I didn’t know this either, I just learned this myself. 🧐

Here’s why:
During a toast as the honoree, it’s improper to raise your own glass, it’s comparable to self-praise. Think about it, someone gives you an award and you pat yourself on the back for being such an amazing person. 😂 
Once all the toasts are over, then you raise your glass and thank everyone for their kind words, and put your glass down.

Same rule applies to a couple at their wedding reception. Traditionally, the bride and groom lift their glasses after the toast to show they appreciate and acknowledge the well-wishes shared.

Were you aware of this rule?

Save and share this post for future reference. 

Here’s my top 5 questions you should ask before hiring a wedding planner. These questions provided cover important aspects, but your “top” questions can vary based on individual preferences:

1. What is your experience with weddings similar to ours, and can you provide references from past clients?
2. What services are included in your wedding planning package, and are there any additional fees we should be aware of?
3. How do you handle communication and collaboration with clients throughout the planning process?
4. Can you walk us through your process for creating and managing a wedding timeline, including potential challenges and solutions?
5. What is your approach to handling unexpected issues or emergencies on the wedding day, and do you have a backup plan in place?

These questions guide you to find the perfect wedding vendors. My aim is to empower you with the right information so you can make informed decisions for your special day, avoiding overpromises and ensuring a seamless experience.

Happy Planning! Like and follow for more wedding tips and techniques.

You’re engaged! Congratulations! NOW WHAT!
First things first… SLOW YOUR ROLL! 😝
Planning is fun but there is a LOT of things to do. 

Here are 3 crucial questions you should discuss with your fiancé before you start planning: 

1.  When do you want to start planning the wedding, immediately or in a month or two?

2. How will we handle wedding opinions from family? Come up with script for your family members and friends to redirect questions you are not ready to answer. 

3. Discuss your wedding budget and finances: How are we paying for the wedding? Are you open to discussing potential debt, and what savings do you currently have? Also, have you considered if there might be contributions from our families?

Still can’t figure it out! Call a planner, we can help you with that! ⭐️
